Raspberry Pi has launched its first brick-and-mortar store – situated in Cambridge, England. Positioned in the Grand Arcade shopping centre, customers will have access to a variety of Pi devices, accessories, and books. The Raspberry Pi store will also offer customers “store-only exclusives, and it will not accept repair or return requests at the store if the product wasn’t purchased there. The Raspberry Pi is a mini-computer designed to be an easy-to-use tool for DIY electronics fanatics, with units like the Pi 3 Model B+ a powerful platform for media and automation. Photos of the new store are below.     